{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|Jas|3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jas","chapter":3,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v11","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jas:3:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jas","bookOrder":58,"chapter":3,"verse":1,"text":"Not many should become teachers, my brothers, because you know that we will receive a stricter judgment.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jas:3:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jas","bookOrder":58,"chapter":3,"verse":2,"text":"For we all stumble in many ways. If anyone does not stumble in what he says, he is mature, able also to control the whole body.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jas:3:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jas","bookOrder":58,"chapter":3,"verse":3,"text":"Now if we put bits into the mouths of horses so that they obey us, we direct their whole bodies.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jas:3:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jas","bookOrder":58,"chapter":3,"verse":4,"text":"And consider ships: Though very large and driven by fierce winds, they are guided by a very small rudder wherever the will of the pilot directs.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jas:3:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jas","bookOrder":58,"chapter":3,"verse":5,"text":"So too, though the tongue is a small part of the body, it boasts great things. Consider how a small fire sets ablaze a large forest.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jas:3:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jas","bookOrder":58,"chapter":3,"verse":6,"text":"And the tongue is a fire. The tongue, a world of unrighteousness, is placed among our members. It stains the whole body, sets the course of life on fire, and is itself set on fire by hell.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jas:3:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jas","bookOrder":58,"chapter":3,"verse":7,"text":"Every kind of animal, bird, reptile, and fish is tamed and has been tamed by humankind,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jas:3:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jas","bookOrder":58,"chapter":3,"verse":8,"text":"but no one can tame the tongue. It is a restless evil, full of deadly poison.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jas:3:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jas","bookOrder":58,"chapter":3,"verse":9,"text":"With the tongue we bless our Lord and Father, and with it we curse people who are made in God’s likeness.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jas:3:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jas","bookOrder":58,"chapter":3,"verse":10,"text":"Blessing and cursing come out of the same mouth. My brothers and sisters, these things should not be this way.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jas:3:11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jas","bookOrder":58,"chapter":3,"verse":11,"text":"Does a spring pour out sweet and bitter water from the same opening?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jas:3:12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jas","bookOrder":58,"chapter":3,"verse":12,"text":"Can a fig tree produce olives, my brothers and sisters, or a grapevine produce figs? Neither can a saltwater spring yield fresh water.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jas:3:13","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jas","bookOrder":58,"chapter":3,"verse":13,"text":"Who among you is wise and understanding? By his good conduct he should show that his works are done in the gentleness that comes from wisdom.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jas:3:14","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jas","bookOrder":58,"chapter":3,"verse":14,"text":"But if you have bitter envy and selfish ambition in your heart, don’t boast and deny the truth.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jas:3:15","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jas","bookOrder":58,"chapter":3,"verse":15,"text":"Such wisdom does not come down from above but is earthly, unspiritual, demonic.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jas:3:16","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jas","bookOrder":58,"chapter":3,"verse":16,"text":"For where there is envy and selfish ambition, there is disorder and every evil practice.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jas:3:17","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jas","bookOrder":58,"chapter":3,"verse":17,"text":"But the wisdom from above is first pure, then peace-loving, gentle, compliant, full of mercy and good fruits, unwavering, without pretense.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jas:3:18","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jas","bookOrder":58,"chapter":3,"verse":18,"text":"And the fruit of righteousness is sown in peace by those who cultivate peace.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"}],"layout":{"bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Jas","chapter":3,"paragraphStarts":[1,13],"headings":[{"beforeVerse":1,"text":"Controlling the Tongue"},{"beforeVerse":13,"text":"The Wisdom from Above"}],"poetryBlocks":[],"studyByVerse":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jas:3:1","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Not many should become teachers, my brothers, "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":1,"text":"Or brothers and sisters"},{"kind":"text","text":" because you know that we will receive a stricter judgment. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mt 23:8","book":"Mat","chapter":23,"verse":8,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 2:20–21","book":"Rom","chapter":2,"verse":20,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Tm 1:7","book":"1Ti","chapter":1,"verse":7,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Mt 23:8","book":"Mat","chapter":23,"verse":8},{"label":"Rm 2:20–21","book":"Rom","chapter":2,"verse":20},{"label":"1Tm 1:7","book":"1Ti","chapter":1,"verse":7}],"footnotes":[{"marker":1,"text":"Or brothers and sisters"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jas:3:2","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"For we all stumble in many ways. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Kg 8:46","book":"1Ki","chapter":8,"verse":46,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Pr 20:9","book":"Pro","chapter":20,"verse":9,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jms 2:10","book":"Jas","chapter":2,"verse":10,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" If anyone does not stumble in what he says, he is mature, able also to control the whole body. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mt 12:37","book":"Mat","chapter":12,"verse":37,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jms 1:26","book":"Jas","chapter":1,"verse":26,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Pt 3:10","book":"1Pe","chapter":3,"verse":10,"letter":"f"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"1Kg 8:46","book":"1Ki","chapter":8,"verse":46},{"label":"Pr 20:9","book":"Pro","chapter":20,"verse":9},{"label":"Jms 2:10","book":"Jas","chapter":2,"verse":10},{"label":"Mt 12:37","book":"Mat","chapter":12,"verse":37},{"label":"Jms 1:26","book":"Jas","chapter":1,"verse":26},{"label":"1Pt 3:10","book":"1Pe","chapter":3,"verse":10}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jas:3:3","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Now if we put bits into the mouths of horses so that they obey us, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ps 32:9","book":"Psa","chapter":32,"verse":9,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ps 39:1","book":"Psa","chapter":39,"verse":1,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" we direct their whole bodies. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Ps 32:9","book":"Psa","chapter":32,"verse":9},{"label":"Ps 39:1","book":"Psa","chapter":39,"verse":1}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jas:3:4","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"And consider ships: Though very large and driven by fierce winds, they are guided by a very small rudder wherever the will of the pilot directs. "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jas:3:5","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"So too, though the tongue is a small part of the body, it boasts great things. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ps 12:3–4","book":"Psa","chapter":12,"verse":3,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ps 73:8–9","book":"Psa","chapter":73,"verse":8,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" Consider how a small fire sets ablaze a large forest. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Ps 12:3–4","book":"Psa","chapter":12,"verse":3},{"label":"Ps 73:8–9","book":"Psa","chapter":73,"verse":8}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jas:3:6","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"And the tongue is a fire. The tongue, a world of unrighteousness, is placed "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":2,"text":"Or places itself, or appoints itself"},{"kind":"text","text":" among our members. It stains the whole body, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ps 120:2–3","book":"Psa","chapter":120,"verse":2,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Pr 16:27","book":"Pro","chapter":16,"verse":27,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mt 15:11","book":"Mat","chapter":15,"verse":11,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mt 15:18","book":"Mat","chapter":15,"verse":18,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"text","text":" sets the course of life on fire, and is itself set on fire by hell. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Ps 120:2–3","book":"Psa","chapter":120,"verse":2},{"label":"Pr 16:27","book":"Pro","chapter":16,"verse":27},{"label":"Mt 15:11","book":"Mat","chapter":15,"verse":11},{"label":"Mt 15:18","book":"Mat","chapter":15,"verse":18}],"footnotes":[{"marker":2,"text":"Or places itself, or appoints itself"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jas:3:7","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Every kind of animal, bird, reptile, and fish is tamed and has been tamed by humankind, "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jas:3:8","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"but no one can tame the tongue. It is a restless evil, full of deadly poison. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ps 140:3","book":"Psa","chapter":140,"verse":3,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ec 10:11","book":"Ecc","chapter":10,"verse":11,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 3:13","book":"Rom","chapter":3,"verse":13,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Ps 140:3","book":"Psa","chapter":140,"verse":3},{"label":"Ec 10:11","book":"Ecc","chapter":10,"verse":11},{"label":"Rm 3:13","book":"Rom","chapter":3,"verse":13}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jas:3:9","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"With the tongue we bless our Lord and Father, and with it we curse people who are made in God’s likeness. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 1:26","book":"Gen","chapter":1,"verse":26,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Co 11:7","book":"1Co","chapter":11,"verse":7,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Gn 1:26","book":"Gen","chapter":1,"verse":26},{"label":"1Co 11:7","book":"1Co","chapter":11,"verse":7}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jas:3:10","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Blessing and cursing come out of the same mouth. My brothers and sisters, these things should not be this way. "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jas:3:11","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Does a spring pour out sweet and bitter water from the same opening? "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jas:3:12","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Can a fig tree produce olives, my brothers and sisters, or a grapevine produce figs? Neither can a saltwater spring yield fresh water."}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Jas:3:13","parts":[{"kind":"t